1-3. Elbow method k 

wssplot <- function(data, nc=15, seed=1234){
  wss <- (nrow(data)-1)*sum(apply(data,2,var))
  for (i in 2:nc){
    set.seed(seed)
    wss[i] <- sum(kmeans(data, centers=i)$withinss)}
  plot(1:nc, wss, type="b", xlab="# of Clusters",
       ylab="Within group sum of squares")}
wssplot(df)

wssplot(df, nc = 6)

k=3 .

2-2. Hierarchical clustering 

d <- dist(df, method = "euclidean") # Euclidean   
H.fit <- hclust(d, method = "ward.D2") # Ward.D2 within-cluster variance 
                                       # hclust      
plot(H.fit) # dendogram 
groups <- cutree(H.fit, k = 3) # cutree(h)  (k)     
rect.hclust(H.fit, k = 3, border = "red") #  (k) 3     

# Confusion matrix
table(wine[,2],groups)
   groups
     1  2  3
  1 59  0  0
  2  6 65  0
  3  0  0 48
